Ghana Aims to Start Work on $6 Billion Rail Network in April, Graphic Says

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-02-15T11:01:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/ghana-aims-to-start-work-on-6-billion-rail-network-in-april-graphic-says.html
Ghana  will start work on a $6
billion project to renovate and expand its rail network in the
east of the country in April, the Daily Graphic reported.  The 1,200-kilometer (746-mile) rail project will link
Nsawam in the south east to Paga in the north east via Kumasi,
the country’s second biggest city, the Accra-based newspaper
said, citing Daniel Markin, chairman of  Ghana  Railway Authority.  Construction will be done by China’s  General Machinery
Import & Export Co.  and  China National Machinery & Equipment
Import & Export Corp.  and funded by the Chinese government, the
Daily Graphic said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 